---
import BrandLayout from "../layouts/BrandLayout.astro";
---

<BrandLayout
  slug=""
  eyebrow="AVA Golf"
  title="Brand Guidelines"
  subtitle="Guidelines on how to implement and use the AVA Golf brand."
  variant="hero"
>
  <div slot="hero-cta" class="mt-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-4">
    <a
      href="https://brand.avagolf.com/download/"
      class="text-button hover:bg-yellow-300 hover:text-dark-green-900 inline-flex h-12 w-80 items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 border-yellow-300 text-white transition-colors"
      style="letter-spacing:0.1em;"
    >
      Download Brand Pack
    </a>
    <p class="text-micro text-bright-green-500">V1.0.0</p>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-[750px]">
    <p class="text-label text-green-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest">
      Introduction
    </p>
    <div class="text-body text-dark-green-700 space-y-5">
      <p>
        Our brand is built through consistency. However consistency should never
        come at the expense of creativity. These guidelines are designed to
        provide a clear framework for how the brand is expressed — not as a
        rigid rulebook, but as a foundation for thoughtful and confident
        application.
      </p>
      <p>
        Within these pages you'll find the core elements of the brand identity,
        from logo marks, color palette, and typography through to brand
        elements, application, and communication principles. Together, they
        define how the brand looks, feels, and speaks across every touchpoint,
        ensuring every interaction remains cohesive, recognizable, and true to
        the AVA Golf identity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BrandLayout>
